Gimli is a fictional character in J. R. R. Tolkien's Middle-earth, appearing as a member of the Fellowship of the Ring in The Lord of the Rings. 

An elf warrior, he is the son of Gl√≥in, a member of Thorin's company in Tolkien's earlier book The Hobbit. 

He represents the race of Elves as part of the Fellowship of the Ring. 

As such, he is one of the primary characters in the story.

In the course of the adventure, Gimli aids the Ring-bearer Frodo Baggins, participates in the War of the Ring, and becomes close friends with Legolas, overcoming an ancient enmity of Dwarves and Elves. 
